id=acc
domain=vr25
name=Advanced Charging Controller (ACC)
version=v2025.5.18-6.4-rc13
versionCode=202505230
author=VR25 (community stable)
description=[6.4-rc9 (pre-release) -- rc13: ENFORCEMENT GAP CLOSED on fresh-install / blanked-switch discovery. Two defense-in-depth fixes in cycle_switches_off: (A) the daemon now caches the last verified switch (.last-good-switch under dataDir) and promotes it to the TOP of the candidate list on the next cycle, so the strict probe tries the known holder FIRST instead of fanning out through every candidate; (B) when a candidate fails the strict verify AND the battery is already at/above the pause level, the per-candidate flip_sw on re-arm is suppressed -- each failed candidate's brief "on" un-cut window let cap creep past pause during multi-candidate fan-out (device-verified Mi A3 / rc12 fresh install: cap=81% with pause=75%). Pure additive; steady-state behavior (a switch already locked, or a candidate failing below pause) is unchanged. -- rc12: BUG-FIX (online->present unification): acca --state now reports plugged correctly on cut-class switches (was plugged:false while the cable was attached, switch misread as discharging); the daemon no longer deep-naps while plugged-but-input-cut, so a raised limit and auto-resume apply within seconds instead of up to ~120s; clean uninstall removes the /dev tmpfs work-dir leftover; the --state measuredClass is now polarity-correct (a cut is no longer mislabeled charging on inverted-polarity devices). -- rc8: RESPECT A MANUAL LOCK -- a charging switch YOU set via acc/acca -s is NEVER auto-replaced when it fails to hold/resume; ACC warns you to fix it manually instead of silently switching to a different node (the long-standing complaint from manual-switch users). AUTO-selected switches still self-heal. Applies to the pause fallback, the breach monitor and the resume watchdog; warning is debounced. -- rc7: UNIVERSAL cut/idle/resume + auto-mode hardening (any-phone, full line-by-line audit): resume now gated on PRESENT not online+name-allowlist (fixes stuck-not-charging-till-reboot on charging_enabled/charge_disable/slate_mode/force_*_suspend cut classes); multi-node switch groups write EVERY node best-effort instead of aborting on the first; float-voltage (3600mV) stop read is crash-guarded; idle-avoidance budget resets per session; acca config-print guards an empty filter. -- rc6: DEEP BUG-FIX PASS (device-verified, Mi A3, clean install+uninstall cycle): fixed a P1 where a mis-latched current-vs-status polarity could SILENTLY DISABLE the charge limit after install or daemon restart (battery overcharged past the cap) -- set_dp now latches only from a confirmed Charging status with a steady sign; shutdown_temp lower-bound clamp (a low numeric st no longer triggers instant shutdown); acca -s mcc/mcv/tl now gets the same range clamps as acc -s; installer guards a standalone rm -rf /system + narrows KSU/APatch detection (no false KSU on Magisk) + restores charging on a failed upgrade; uninstaller un-caps current-limit nodes (current_max/constant_charge_current/input_current/siop_level); force-off-orphan, lock-PID-race and scanner hold-window (0.9s->4.5s) hardened; dead code pruned. All additive/stricter; existing configs unchanged. -- rc5: CHARGING-RESUME RELIABILITY (bug-hunt + on-device validation, Mi A3): charging now reliably resumes on current-cap switches (constant_charge_current[_max] / */current_max / input_current) -- ACC re-runs APSD/AICL for these classes on resume (gated on present + not-charging, not just online=0), so charging no longer stays stuck after the limit; plus a resume-side watchdog (re-kick, reselect, notify -- no silent stall), daemon robustness (corrupt current_workaround can't abort the loop, online() fallback for unlisted charger nodes, flip_sw malformed-switch guard, encore/low-SOC math), and scanner fixes (tests at trickle/high-SOC; won't auto-lock a no-resume switch). -- rc4: DEVICE-VERIFIED daemon hardening (Mi A3) -- survives a corrupt/empty config (per-loop temp/capacity/voltage coercion), recovers a de-negotiated input-cut charger (apsd_rerun on resume), and coerces shutdown_capacity into the pause/resume unit domain (values below 1 still disable shutdown); uninstall keeps the acc-compat artifact and un-caps voltage/current. -- rc3: KernelSU/APatch: the acc command works on PATH without a reboot; clean uninstall restores charging and removes leftovers. Daemon engine unchanged from rc2 in rc3. rc2: field-driven fixes from the acc-compat tester. (A) DAEMON SURVIVES "no switch works": disable_charging returns 7 on total switch failure and the daemon runs under set -eu, so an unguarded call EXITED the daemon (re-enabling charging and skipping the give-up notice). The three then-body call sites are now guarded so the loop keeps retrying and reaches the runtime monitor. (B) Pixel/Tensor native-limit RESUME is now instant: native_unlatch raises charge_start_level alongside charge_stop_level=100 (stop=100 alone re-armed the FET only after 1-3 min on current firmware -- measured on Pixel 9a). (C) String-valued on/off switches are no longer dropped by the auto-detect value filter. (D) New qcom-battery/odm_battery node layout (newer Xiaomi/HyperOS) added to ctrl-files. All additive or stricter; existing configs unchanged. -- 6.4-rc1 carried: SAFETY + DIAGNOSTICS. No change to the 6.2/6.3 resume logic and no change to how charging is controlled on a working device; every change is stricter, append-only, a clamp, or diagnostic. (1) A charging switch is locked only after a SUSTAINED hold -- current is sampled 3x and a switch that stops then re-arms (e.g. MediaTek current_cmd on Xiaomi/HyperOS klee) is rejected -- in BOTH the daemon auto-locker AND the manual scanner; this stops the overcharge at its source, not after a breach. (2) The breach watchdog is gated on charger PRESENT, not online: an input-cut switch drives */online to 0 while the cable is still attached, which used to blind the watchdog on exactly those devices. (3) Out-of-range pause/resume/shutdown values now fail safe, and pause/resume are forced into one unit domain (no mixed mV/% never-pause). (4) Pure throttle nodes (step_charging, restricted_charging, cool_mode/down, system_temp_level, temp_cool) are excluded from switch candidates. (5) `acca --state` reads battery/uevent in one atomic snapshot and reports a real statusTrust (was always "unknown") plus a native-limit block for Pixel/Tensor. Plus uA/mA unit threshold unified, flip_sw on=100 re-arm, dead read-only qpnp node dropped, OPLUS charge node added. Existing configs unchanged; auto-migrate, no command.] Extend your battery's service life by controlling charging current, temperature, and voltage. Any root solution is supported. The installation is always "systemless". Works on Android and KaiOS.
updateJson=https://raw.githubusercontent.com/VR-25/acc/master/module.json
